# SwiftUI typography (Intrinsic Design)

**Source:** `tokens/foundation.json` · `patterns/TYPOGRAPHY.md` · ADR-011

## Use semantic roles

```swift
import IntrinsicDesign

Text("Title").font(IntrinsicTypography.headline)
Text("Detail").font(IntrinsicTypography.body)
Text("2h ago").font(IntrinsicTypography.footnote).foregroundStyle(.secondary)
```

`IntrinsicTypography` maps to Apple `Font.TextStyle` — Dynamic Type scales automatically.

## Hard bans in feature code

- ❌ `.font(.system(size:))` or raw `CGFloat` point sizes
- ❌ Custom font files for UI chrome (system fonts only unless ADR exception)
- ❌ Shrinking `.body` for de-emphasis — use `footnote`, `caption`, or `.secondary`

## Hierarchy

| Surface | Role |
|---------|------|
| List row primary | `headline` |
| List row subtitle | `subheadline` |
| Timestamp / legal | `footnote` |
| Section header | `label` |
| Default paragraph | `body` |

## Keystone / admin

iOS admin surfaces follow the same Text Style rules. Web Keystone uses theme tokens — not `IntrinsicTypography` pixel equivalents.
